    "body": "@codeshocks oh, pretty everywhere :-)\r\n- from the fact: that our db (MDBX) can't reduce in size even that you deleted data (it can, but probability is low - depends on fragmentation). To reduce db size will need additional stepÂ (with additional disk space): \"mdbx_dump/mdbx_load\" or \"integration mdbx_to_mdbx\" which will copy data to new db.\r\n- to the fact: that such feature will add tons of new corner-cases and scenarios which will increase maintenance cost: every Bug-report I will need to clarify - how people did sync first, and what they changed later, and when they changed, and what version of Erigon they used when changed mode, etc... \r\n- and need protect users from \"added --prune flag by human-mistake and lost all data\" case\r\n",
